# Power Automate Deploy Guide: {{ display_name }}

**Workflow:** `{{ workflow_name }}`
**Description:** {{ description }}
**Cron schedule:** `{{ cron_expression }}` (translated to PA Recurrence: every {{ recurrence_interval }} {{ recurrence_frequency | lower }})
**Generated:** {{ registration_date }}

This guide walks you through importing `flow_import.zip` into Microsoft Power Automate and wiring the placeholder action to your real system.

***

## Step 1 - Import the ZIP

1. Open https://flow.microsoft.com and sign in to the environment where you want the flow to live.
2. Navigate to **My flows** (left nav) > **Import** > **Import Package (Legacy)**.
3. Upload `flow_import.zip`.
4. On the **Import setup** screen, confirm the flow name (`{{ display_name }}`) and click **Import**.
5. Power Automate creates the flow in a **Saved** state.

## Step 2 - Wire the placeholder action

The generated flow contains a placeholder HTTP action named `Run_Yigthinker_Workflow`. Replace it:

- **Option A (recommended):** Delete the placeholder and add a **Run a Child Flow** action pointing to your existing data-processing flow.
- **Option B (Dataverse):** Replace with a **Perform an unbound action** targeting your Dataverse automation.
- **Option C (HTTP to Yigthinker Gateway):** Keep the HTTP action and update the URI to your Yigthinker Gateway endpoint.

## Step 3 - Turn the flow on

1. Open the flow in Power Automate.
2. Click **Edit** > **Save**.
3. Back on the flow detail page, click **Turn on**.
4. Wait for the next scheduled trigger or click **Run** > **Run now** to test.

## Step 4 - Monitor runs

- **Runs history:** flow detail page > **All runs** tab.
- **Failures:** PA sends an email to the flow owner if 3 consecutive runs fail.

***

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Import fails with "Invalid package" | Confirm the ZIP contains `Microsoft.Flow/flows/{{ workflow_name }}/definition.json` (use `unzip -l flow_import.zip`). |
| Flow is Saved but not running | Click **Turn on** - imported flows default to off. |
| Trigger never fires | Double-check the Recurrence settings match `{{ cron_expression }}` after import. |

